<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16602] Revise the metrics docs in the website</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16602</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While inspecting the metrics code, I realized that the metrics docs (at &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/latest/operating/metrics.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/latest/operating/metrics.html&lt;/a&gt;) has several errors, e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.	JMX MBean names have incorrect format. They should be separated with commas, but the doc has space separated values. Cassandra users referring to this docs will not get it working. &lt;br/&gt;
2.	The MBean name for Keyspace metrics is wrong. In the code, we have `keyspace=&amp;lt;Keyspace&amp;gt;`, instead of `scope=&amp;lt;Keyspace&amp;gt;`, which is listed in the docs page. &lt;br/&gt;
3.	There are outdated fields. For instance, the `SyncTime` has been renamed to `RepairSyncTime` under the TableMetrics. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To avoid frustrating and confusing the users that refer to the metrics page, the docs need to be revised.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
